Class StandardSummaryTableModel

All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, TableModel
public class StandardSummaryTableModel
extends SummaryTableModel

StandardSummaryTableModel is the subclass of SummaryTableModel used for tables derived from non-pairwise IDEA analyses (those with at least one dataset having three or more sequences). These analyses differ from pairwise analyses in that there are multiple models for each dataset. StandardSummaryTableModel provides methods for sorting the models within datasets, determining the likeliest model for a dataset and obtaining a list of the values in a numerical column using only a given model or using the likeliest model for each dataset.

numericalValuesInColumn

public LinkedList<Double> numericalValuesInColumn(int column,
                                                  String model)
The numericalValuesInColumn method returns a linked list of the values in the requested column (which should be a numeric column). This is useful for making histograms. Only values in rows matching the given model are included in the returned list. If LIKELIEST is given as the model, the values for the likeliest model for each dataset are used.

Specified by:
numericalValuesInColumn in class SummaryTableModel
Parameters:
column - the requested column
model - the model to restrict results to, or LIKELIEST
Returns:
a linked list of values in the requested column

leftmostColumnToDisplayAsSelected

public int leftmostColumnToDisplayAsSelected()
Row selection is indicated on the table by displaying an outline around all or some of the row's cells. The leftMostColumnToDisplayAsSelected method returns the index of the leftmost column to be included in the outlined area when a row is selected. StandardSummaryTableModel's implementation returns the index of the Model column because the columns to the left of it contain values that span multiple rows.

Specified by:
leftmostColumnToDisplayAsSelected in class SummaryTableModel
Returns:
the index of the Model column

showHistogram

public void showHistogram(int column,
                          JFrame ownerWindow)
The showHistogram method is called when the user requests a histogram. StandardSummaryTableModel's implementation brings up a HistogramDialog, which allows the user to select a model on which to base the histogram. NOTE: This is a button method. See class SummaryTableButton.

Specified by:

sortAscending

public void sortAscending(int columnIndex,
                          JFrame ownerWindow)
The sortAscending method sorts within each dataset (rather than across datasets) in ascending order of the specified parameter. Numeric values appear in ascending order above string values, which appear in ascending order above non-numeric, non-string values. This method modifies the underlying data structure. NOTE: This is a button method. See class SummaryTableButton.

Parameters:
columnIndex - the index of the column on which to sort
ownerWindow - ignored; may be null (This parameter exists for all button methods since some may require it.)
